## Installation Script

### Preparation Steps

Install the following additional products:

~~~
sudo apt-get install dblatex docbook-xsl docbook-utils libxml2-utils texlive-font-utils
~~~

Set (only once) the following rewrite rule

~~~
git config --global url."git://github.com/ghc/packages-".insteadOf git://github.com/ghc/packages/ 
~~~


The following software must be available and on the correct version

~~~
cabal --version
clang --version
happy --version
~~~

### Installation

Note: The *ghchead* at the end of the clone command, is the name of the target directory.

~~~
cd ~/Projekte
git clone --recursive git://git.haskell.org/ghc.git ghc-head
cd ghc-head
cd mk
cp build.mk.sample build.mk
atom build.mk
~~~

Remove the comment marker (#) on the line "BuildFlavor = devel2"

~~~
cd ..
./boot
./configure
make -j4
~~~

## Do a first little test

~~~
./inplace/bin/ghc-stage2 --version
~~~

## Make the GHC Head compiler usable 

* Create a directory _Software/ghc-head/bin_ 
* Create a link to the new compiler: _ln -s  /home/roland/Projekte/ghchead/inplace/bin/ghc-stage2 /home/roland/Software/ghc-head/bin/ghc_
* Use _swithcghc head_ to mkae the new compiler the default compiler